Recent legislation has required school districts to develop a Learning Continuity and Attendance Plan. Pioneer Union Elementary School District is seeking your input on a variety of issues to inform the development of the plan. If you would like a paper version of the input-form, please contact your child's school to request one.

post_text:
The Pioneer Elementary School District will be serving meals during the time of Distance Learning. Meals will be distributed at Frontier Elementary School located at
1854 N. Mustang Drive
Meals will be distributed on Mondays and Thursdays each week from 11:00 - 12:30. Meals will be served in a "Grab and Go" fashion and can be picked up by drive-through at the bus loading zone on the Frontier Elementary School Campus.

Please complete this form each week by Sunday evening so that meals may be prepared for your children and ready for pick-up.

Mondays - 3 days of meals will be served
Thursdays - 2 days of meals will be served.
Parents will pre-order breakfast, lunch, or both meals for each day.
Order form link: https://forms.gle/st7mSSuY52zajZd7A

This order form can also be found on our home page in the Departments section, under Food Services.

6th Grade Parents,
The new 6th grade Chromebooks arrived sooner than expected. We need you to come in and exchange the Chromebook and charging cable that you checked out for your new device. We will be doing the exchange in the middle school cafeteria this week. Please click the link below to schedule an appointment.
https://calendar.google.com/calendar/selfsched?sstoken=UUlXdmUyQkZUQjZQfGRlZmF1bHR8YzU0OTkxYWMyNGUzZTc2MTNlNWMwNTE3Y2EwOTFiNzE

Remember to bring the Chromebook and the charging cable. We won't be able to make the exchange without both.
Please schedule an appointment as soon as possible. The new Chromebook is faster and will perform better during distance learning.

If you currently have a Chromebook with a hot pink barcode sticker on the back, then you already have a new device and no further action is needed.
If you have any questions, please contact Kim Allein at kallein@puesd.net.

post_text:
Dear Pioneer Community,

Today, Governor Newsom unveiled details about the revised guidance for opening schools amid the COVID-19 pandemic. The guidelines require a county to meet specific criteria in order for schools to open for in-person instruction. If the county does not meet the criteria, school districts must provide rigorous instruction through distance learning. Kings County does not meet the criteria to open its schools to on-campus instruction. We have conducted a significant amount of planning for the return to school, including the distance learning model. More information about our distance learning model will be provided in the weeks to come. Instruction will begin on August 19.

We are committed to serving our students and community to the highest degree under any model of instructional delivery we must provide during the COVID-19 pandemic. Pioneer will continue to energetically pursue our mission and live up to our maxim, “A Learning Community Dedicated to Excellence!”

post_text:
Attention Parents Who Need To Register a Student
for the 2020-2021 School Year

Pioneer Union Elementary School District will open
online registration on July 18th, 2020.

Please begin to collect the documentation that you will need to complete the registration process.

-Household information -- address and phone numbers, including two address verification documentation
-Parent information -- work and cell phone numbers, email addresses
-Student information -- demographic and health/medication information, including birth certificate and proof of required immunizations.
* If your child does not have the required immunizations, please take them to their doctor as soon as possible. Children cannot be enrolled without their required shots.
-Emergency Contacts - phone numbers, relationship to student(s), contact order

If you need assistance, please call the district office at (559) 585-2400. In-person district office visits will be by appointment only. All visitors will be required to wear a mask.

Our dearest Pioneer students,

We have a few weeks left of school and we have all had significant changes in our lives. This week’s Community Connections activity is a COVID-19 Time Capsule. Hanford Parks and Recreation Department posted it to their Facebook page a few days ago. You can print it and fill in the many different sections. When we all look back at this time frame next year, or a few years from now, this Time Capsule will allow us to see where we were and how much we have changed. Keep your chin up!! We are here for you!!



In health and well-being,



Tye Fletcher, School Psychologist

Rebecca Harper, District Registered Nurse

Mary Stake, Counselor

Congratulations Frontier Elementary!!!
Superintendent, Paul van Loon and Frontier staff members Principal Tenci Murillo-Brown, Anna Teliha, Elaine Hoover and Lois Bentley receive the California Distinguished School Award from State Superintendent of Public Instruction Tony Thurmond at the award ceremony held on February 10.
